Author: zachbeane
Content: Older versions of hunchentoot (named TBNL) used mod_lisp and mod_lisp2 to communicate requests to the Lisp side in a simplified form (similar to FastCGI). Since Hunchentoot can speak HTTP directly now, mod_proxy is effectively the same as mod_lisp for hunchentoot's purposes. mod_lisp is not an embedded interpreter in Apache.

Author: zachbeane
Content:
Hunchentoot is fast enough for many purposes. http://wigflip.com/ has been #1 on delicious a few times without straining my hunchentoot instance.

Comparing it to a Python webserver is not all that useful, since Hunchentoot is typically compiled to machine code.
